{"word":"G156 - αἰτία - aitía - ahee-tee'-a - Accusation","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">αἰτία</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>aitía"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>ahee-tee'-a"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Accusation"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"காரணம், குற்றம், காரியம் - பெண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"1. cause, reason"},{"paragraph":"2. cause for which one is worthy of punishment; crime of which one is accused"},{"paragraph":"3. charge of crime, accusation"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Feminine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (பெண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> From the same as <a href=\"#/G154 - αἰτέω - aitéō - ahee-teh'-o/154\">G154</a>; a <i>cause</i> (as if <i>asked</i> for), that is, (logical) <i>reason</i> (motive, matter), (legal) <i>crime</i> (alleged or proved): - accusation, case, cause, crime, fault, [wh-]ere[-fore]."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"}]}